32:45.540 --> 32:49.270
Another ten minutes, and Adam thinks he is full to the brim.

32:50.880 --> 32:52.130
Yeah I feel a lot of pressure.

32:52.130 --> 32:54.510
However the ultrasound identifies room

32:54.510 --> 32:56.430
for even further extension.

32:56.430 --> 32:58.910
Ok. I am gonna drink a little more water.

32:59.080 --> 33:02.280
100 mills, and five minutes later,

33:02.280 --> 33:04.490
Adam really is myth busting.

33:04.490 --> 33:07.160
I really, really, really need to go.

33:07.160 --> 33:08.950
But before he goes,

33:09.580 --> 33:11.430
I am ready for the full bladder test.

33:11.430 --> 33:13.870
Jamie wants to outline the scoring system,

33:13.900 --> 33:17.230
in excruciatingly slow detail.

33:17.360 --> 33:18.710
The way we're gonna score this test is

33:18.710 --> 33:20.510
Adam starts out with 100 points.

33:20.510 --> 33:22.080
Every time he does something wrong,

33:22.080 --> 33:23.780
we subtract some points.

33:23.840 --> 33:26.200
Now each cone is worth five points.

33:26.210 --> 33:27.120
Oh, my god.

33:27.120 --> 33:29.750
I can't even tell you how badly I have to pee right now.

33:29.760 --> 33:34.970
Every time he screws up the test, that's 20 points.

