And every mile per hour over the speed limit he goes,

33:39.450 --> 33:41.030
that's 5 points.

33:41.030 --> 33:42.180
Let's do it.

33:42.430 --> 33:43.970
Pedestrians that he can hit,

33:43.970 --> 33:46.370
well, let's just say that's a lot of points.

33:46.370 --> 33:48.190
We'll worry about that when we get there.

33:48.470 --> 33:55.620
- Bladder control test in 3...2... - He's such a...

33:56.130 --> 34:00.780
- Man, I am gonna get even. - One.

34:08.940 --> 34:12.620
In 2006, a team of scientists at Wake Forest University

34:12.620 --> 34:15.659
created the world's first lab-grown bladder

34:15.659 --> 34:18.980
and successfully transplanted it into a human.

34:20.690 --> 34:23.110
Two crash tests have proved it.

34:23.710 --> 34:26.340
Super adhesive is no seat belt.

34:27.909 --> 34:29.070
Not yet.

34:30.130 --> 34:31.580
So far we have been having no luck

34:31.580 --> 34:33.530
with our super adhesive seat belt myth.

34:33.530 --> 34:36.040
The failures are in the clothing the dummies were wearing

34:36.040 --> 34:37.940
or in the seats themselves.

34:37.940 --> 34:39.929
What we need to do is focus on

34:39.929 --> 34:42.480
the strength of the bond of the glue.

34:42.520 --> 34:44.370
We're doing that by giving the

34:44.370 --> 34:48.130
glue an ideal bonding surface--two steel plates.

34:48.130 --> 34:49.900
One's gonna go on the dummy's back,

34:49.900 --> 34:53.420
and the other is going to go on a special new metal seat

34:53.420 --> 34:55.630
that I'll be installing into the vehicle.

34:55.630 --> 34:58.050
By taking the fabrics out of the equation,

34:58.060 --> 34:59.950
the guys are putting the glue

34:59.950 --> 35:03.150
and glue alone to the ultimate crash test.

35:03.300 --> 35:05.080
May not be the most comfortable seat.

35:05.080 --> 35:08.680
But if it works, Buster's gonna be glad he has it.

35:10.020 --> 35:11.090
We're back at the runway,

35:11.100 --> 35:12.530
and we're all set up for another crash.

35:12.530 --> 35:13.720
Because we wanna find out

35:13.720 --> 35:16.150
if just the bond from super adhesive

35:16.210 --> 35:18.780
can withstand the forces of a car crash.

